<?xml version='1.0' encoding="ISO-8859-1"?>
<chapter id="config_vars">

    <title>YDConfig variables</title>

    <para>This chapter gives you an overview of all the different configuration variables that are exposed in the different modules. All these configuration settings can be changed using the <link linkend="ydconfig"><literal>YDConfig</literal></link> module.</para>

    <sect1 id="config_vars_ydf2init">

        <title>YDF2_init.php</title>

        <para>These are the configuration variables that are defined in the <literal>YDF2_init.php</literal> file.</para>

        <table pgwide="1">
            <title>Configuration variables for <literal>YDF2_init.php</literal></title>
            <tgroup cols="3" align="left">
                <colspec colname='c1' colwidth="1*" />
                <colspec colname='c2' colwidth="2*" />
                <colspec colname='c3' colwidth="1*" />
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry valign="top">Name</entry>
                        <entry valign="top">Description</entry>
                        <entry valign="top">Default</entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry valign="top">YD_LOCALE</entry>
                        <entry valign="top">The locale used for the current request.</entry>
                        <entry valign="top"><literal>'en'</literal></entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry valign="top">YD_EXECUTOR</entry>
                        <entry valign="top">The name of the class used to execute the request.</entry>
                        <entry valign="top"><literal>'YDExecutor'</literal></entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry valign="top">YD_DEBUG</entry>
                        <entry valign="top">The debugging level for the current request. This influences the amount of debug information that is shown and how.</entry>
                        <entry valign="top"><literal>0</literal></entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>

    </sect1>

